  "text": "The error-adjusted matrix proposed by Olofsson et al. in terms of proportion of area and estimates of producer's accuracy (PA), user's accuracy (UA), and overall accuracy (OA) with 95% confidence intervals was used to evaluate the accuracy of our rubber plantation map in 2015 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The error-adjusted matrix was a statistically robust and transparent approach for assessing accuracy, a method, which has recently become common practice [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
